Zandile Mafe made a short appearance in the Cape Town magistrate’s court. His lawyer was expecting him to be served with an indictment and a High Court date for his trial to begin. Instead, the state informed the court that a final report regarding the damage to Parliament will only be presented by the Department of Public Works to the portfolio committee on 20 May. Ayesha Ismail has the latest for us. #DStv403 CAPE TOWN - Another delay in the trial of Zandile Mafe, the man accused of trying to burn down Parliament. The state was meant to have all its ducks in a row by now, but crucial reports relevant to the trial are still outstanding. READ: Parliament Fire | Mafe bail application postponed The matter has now been postponed to 9 June for all investigations to be completed. Mafe faces multiple charges including arson and terrorism. READ: Parliament fire | Mafe's lawyer wants confession thrown out He has been remanded in custody as he waits for the outcome of his bail appeal. * eNCA's Ayesha Ismail reports.